

■Skill Assessment
<Task>
1. Create an AI tool which generates images based on the prompt provided.
2. Demonstrate how the tool works during the next session.

<Prompt>
"American teenagers having fun at a party."

<Art Style>
Semi-3D Anime style. Please see the attachments for the reference.

■Preparation
1. Core Requirements
Python: Version 3.8 or higher is required.

Hardware Note: While a GPU is preferred for performance, you can run the tasks on a CPU by using quantized models or low-resolution settings.

2. Local LLM Setup
Please ensure you have a local LLM environment ready. You can choose one of the following options:

Option A (Ollama): Install Ollama and pre-pull a lightweight model.

Recommended: llama3.2 or phi3.

Option B (Transformers): Use the transformers library with a small model capable of running on your machine.

3. Image Generation (Stable Diffusion)
You will be using Stable Diffusion for part of the assessment.

Library: Please install diffusers and accelerate.

Models: Pre-download a model suitable for the art style indicated with the attachment (Please see "Sample").

Performance: If you do not have a dedicated GPU, please ensure your script is configured for CPU inference and consider testing with a lower iteration count/resolution to save time.

Constraint:
Local environment:
MACBOOK M1 32GB MEMORY